{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-opus-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_012jArBztVxums3d4AdmR5Zp", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "I have all the context I need. Here's the complete implementation:\n\n## Implementation\n\n### New file: `config/monitoring/prometheus-rule.yaml`\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: monitoring.coreos.com/v1\nkind: PrometheusRule\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: metrics\n    app.kubernetes.io/created-by: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/part-of: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: kustomize\n  name: alerting-rules\n  namespace: system\nspec:\n  groups:\n    - name: multiarch-tuning-operator.rules\n      rules:\n        - alert: MultiarchImageInspectionFailureRateCritical\n          expr: |\n            (\n              rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total[5m])\n              /\n              rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total[5m])\n            ) > 0.05\n          for: 5m\n          labels:\n            severity: critical\n          annotations:\n            message: >-\n              The multiarch tuning operator image inspection failure rate\n              has exceeded 5% over the last 5 minutes.\n              Current value is {{ $value | humanizePercentage }}.\n```\n\n### New file: `config/monitoring/kustomization.yaml`\n\n```yaml\nresources:\n- prometheus-rule.yaml\n```\n\n### Modification to: `config/default/kustomization.yaml`\n\nAdd the monitoring resource to the `resources:` list. Add this line after `- ../webhook`:\n\n```yaml\n- ../monitoring\n```\n\nSo the `resources:` block becomes:\n\n```yaml\nresources:\n- ../crd\n- ../rbac\n- ../manager\n- ../webhook\n- ../monitoring\n```\n\n## Explanation\n\n**Metrics used:**\n- `mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total` \u2014 counter incremented in `internal/controller/podplacement/pod_model.go:502` on each failed image inspection\n- `mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total` \u2014 counter incremented in `internal/controller/podplacement/pod_reconciler.go:88` for each pod processed by the controller\n\n**PromQL expression:** Computes the per-second failure rate over a 5-minute window divided by the per-second pod processing rate over the same window. Using `rate()` on both counters ensures the division produces a ratio (0\u20131). The alert fires when that ratio exceeds 0.05 (5%) and has been above threshold for 5 continuous minutes (`for: 5m`).\n\n**Commands to run:**\n\n```bash\n# Create the monitoring directory\nmkdir -p config/monitoring\n\n# Then create the two files above in config/monitoring/\n\n# Verify kustomize can build the full config\nkustomize build config/default\n```\n\nNo Makefile changes are needed \u2014 `kustomize build` will pick up the new directory through the existing kustomization chain."}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 426, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 581, "cache_read_input_tokens": 38944, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 581, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 1}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "1541a008-9c19-4dbd-97bb-55941dfb9fb0", "uuid": "bc686a7c-a3fb-49b0-8db3-4e28a0294307", "request_id": "req_vrtx_011Cd3uzVnh9AfAiWsLypa2g", "timestamp": "2026-07-15T13:22:48.888Z"}
